RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PICK BYMY FRIEND Perfectly maneuvered to rail in run to first turn, saw opening created by L'ARACHIDE at the seven-sixteenths pole and moved through to a clear lead, shook clear from the field, never in doubt from that point in a dominant effort. BUFFUM'S BEAUTY Stalked three wide into the first turn, prodded by rider to pursue blitzing leader at the three-eighths pole, always chasing an easy winner, clearly bested the rest. LITTLEQUEENOFMEAN Vied two wide into the first turn, became uncomfortable by inner and outer rivals around the three-eighths pole, re-engaged to chase on the inner paths, evenly to the wire. IGO Advanced three wide from the second flight shortly after moving into the first turn, called upon to keep pace at the quarter pole while moving in the four path, move flattened out through the lane. MISS MY MAMMA Established position on the rail in the second flight, never got involved. DYNAMIC WOMAN Settled well in the second grouping around the first bend but shortly before the move to the backstretch started to become rank, got out sharply, always detached from there and not pushed on in the run home. L'ARACHIDE Flashed early speed along the rail, drifted out around the opening bend and allowed PICK BYMY FRIEND to move through at the seven-sixteenths pole, maintained positioning along the rail, backed out at the quarter pole.

ENTRY.NAME: L'Arachide
ENTRY.COMMENT: Flashed on inner, allowed rival inside, backed out 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: Pick Bymy Friend
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2nd flight rail 1st, move lead 7/16, shook clear, never in doubt

ENTRY.COMMENT: Rank between, got out first, always detached

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.

CLAIM.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent

RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUEEN OF LOVE Kept runaway leader in view from the outset, settled in the two path, began to fully commence at the quarter pole, threatened two wide, moved to a narrow lead at the eighth pole, grinded through lane to victory. BREXTON Stalked in the three path well off the leader, moved at the five-sixteenths to challenge three wide, idled from the eighth to the sixteenth pole on the wrong lead, could not match the rally of the winner. HULA KING Fluidly strode to the lead without any rivals joining, opened up on field through the backstretch, two rivals approached on the outside at the quarter pole and rider got to work, fought along willingly on the rail, did not have enough to hold on. FOCUS FIRST Let top flight runners head out and then proceeded towards the rail, tracked off the pace well inside of a rival, pressed along without much response at the quarter pole while traveling in the four path, never a threat to the top trio. INCLUDE HOO Was always detached in the rear and never improved position.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Purse 9300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MARCH 5, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALEX'S GIRL Hopped at the break, quickly hustled to the lead and cleared off rivals, held position in the two path, challenge from inside rival came at the five-sixteenths pole, repelled that challenger, joined by outside rival at the sixteenth, outlasted all comers. TEXAS LONG BOW Carried four wide onto the backside, maintained path to the turn where he commenced a four wide bid at the quarter pole, continued to challenge, carried on wrong lead to the sixteenth, lifted hard, not enough time. ROYAL TAP In tight into the first turn, rank behind rivals, found clean air on the rail and advanced through to challenge ALEX'S GIRL at the three-eighths pole, two path down the lane, evenly. EL CHUMELITO Two wide in move to backside, moved up in the three path beginning at the quarter pole, rivals moved up so he dove to the rail for the stretch, brief rally in lane, nothing left. KICK IT Out the back, never menaced, passed one tiring. TRIPDOWNMEMORYLANE Three wide onto backstretch, dropped out around three-eighths pole, tired home.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 8 4F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 8100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 5, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR EMPIRE Sent to challenge inside around the quarter pole, dueled from that marker around the turn and through the lane, held a narrow lead down the stretch, won the battle. BAJA BRIDGE Lagged behind much quicker rivals, never involved and never fired.
